    {
      "id": "7afde403_eeb984d5",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-simulators/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/simulators/CdsSimulator.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": null,
      "message": "I'm still not sure what is the purpose of the wrapper thread?  What is the problem it's trying to solve?  The original start() method simply invoked server.start().  Do we not want to wait for that to complete?  For that matter, if it throws an exception, then I would think we'd want the simulators to shut down.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-10-13 14:02:10.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "c86830a4_b4f25d02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "32ad8ef4_700f9490",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-simulators/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/simulators/CdsSimulator.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": null,
      "message": "The grpc server uses daemon threads by default. Hence the application will exit as soon the main thread completes. That is why we need awaitTermination to keep the main thread alive until the server is terminated.\n\nWhen awaitTermination is just called without running this as a separate thread, it was messing up other simulators to start up, for example dmaap or aai simulator will not work as the main thread gets kind of stuck waiting for the gRPC server to finish. That is why the gRPC server is run in a separate thread.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4903,
        "name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "display_name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "email": "ajith.sreekumar@bell.ca",
        "username": "a.sreekumar"
      },
      "updated": "2020-10-13 14:21:56.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "7afde403_eeb984d5",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "128eb46e_dd30d452",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-simulators/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/simulators/CdsSimulator.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": null,
      "message": "Thanks for explaining.  Perhaps add a comment to the start() method indicating that we have to wrap the server in a non-daemon thread to prevent the Main thread from exiting prematurely.\n\nMight also want to have start() invoke server.start() directly, and all that wrapper thread would do then is invoke awaitTermination().  That way, any exceptions from server.start() are propagated out of start().",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-10-13 14:29:46.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "32ad8ef4_700f9490",
      "unresolved": true
    },
